    "image_with_text_FAfVaW": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_tfc8jA": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q</strong>: What’s one local item in the shop you think everyone needs to try at least once?</p><p><strong>A: </strong> That’s a tough one. I really stand behind everything we stock. But if I had to pick, I’d say the <em>Crackin’ Bacon</em> from the team at Crack On is a must try. It’s a total game changer. Once you’ve had it, it’s hard to go back to any other bacon.</p><p><strong>Q: </strong>How would you describe your personal style?</p><p><strong>A: </strong> Fit is important to me. I like to keep it clean and simple with solid colours and a well-put-together look. Most of the time I fly under the radar, but I’ll throw in a pop of something fun every now and then.</p><p><strong>Q:</strong>Has working in a space that blends food, design, and community influenced the way you dress or shop?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> I think so. I work long days, so comfort is key but I still want to look presentable and approachable. Being in this kind of environment definitely makes me more thoughtful about style and quality.  </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_tfc8jA"
      ],
